gw.pl.util

Class StaticInt

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.pl.util.StaticInt

  • public abstract class StaticInt
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class that keeps a static pool of Integer objects for the integer values from -1 up into the small thousands. Use get(int) to look up an already-allocated integer value in the pool.
    Author:
    mshaw

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static java.lang.Integer get(int i)
        Get a static integers object from a range of pre-created Integers in the INTEGER_POOL. If the int value is outside the pool range a new Integer object is created.

        Use this method so that new Integer objects, particularly entity keys, states and types, don't have to be created every time an Integer is stored or read from the database.

        Parameters:
        i - Int value
        Returns:
        An Integer object
